Machine with Concrete — Arthur Ganson

Machine with Concrete | Exploratorium

Legendary kinetic and mechanical sculptor Arthur Ganson has lent us one of his simplest and most potent works. A motor is connected to a block of concrete via a simple system of gears. The final gear, embedded in concrete, is set up to make one revolution once every 13.7 billion years, yet the machine whirs uninterrupted.

LEGO automata synth

Alex Allmont

Play House

Alex Allmont
Play House is an automata that generates slow hypnotic acid house through mechanisms built from LEGO Technic. This piece was made for AudioGraft 2014 with a commission from Oxford Contemporary Music. Thanks to Danny Chapman and Gareth Ardron for cameras, and Vic Bosher & the OCM team for support!
